quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  20,1,Ta Ha
  20,2,We have not sent down the Koran upon thee for thee to be unprosperous
  20,3,but only as a reminder to him who tears
  20,4,a revelation from Him who created the earth and the high heavens
  20,5,the All-compassionate sat Himself upon the Throne; to Him belongs
  20,6,"all that is in the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, and all that is underneath the soil"
  20,7,"Be thou loud in thy speech, yet surely He knows the secret and that yet more hidden"
  20,8,God -- there is no god but He. To Him belong the Names Most Beautiful
  20,9,Hast thou received the story of Moses
  20,10,"When he saw a fire, and said to his family, 'Tarry you here; I observe a fire. Perhaps I shall bring you a brand from it, or I shall find at the fire guidance"
  20,11,"When he came to it, a voice cried, 'Moses"
  20,12,"I am thy Lord; put off thy shoes; thou art in the holy valley, Towa"
  20,13,I Myself have chosen thee; therefore give thou ear to this revelation
  20,14,"Verily I am God; there is no god but I; therefore serve Me, and perform the prayer of My remembrance"
  20,15,The Hour is coming; I would conceal it that every soul may be recompensed for its labours
  20,16,"Let none bar thee from it, that believes not in it but follows after his own caprice, or thou wilt perish"
  20,17,"What is that, Moses, thou hast in thy right hand"
  20,18,"Why, it is my staff,' said Moses. 'I lean upon it, and with it I beat down leaves to feed my sheep; other uses also I find in it"
  20,19,"Said He, 'Cast it down, Moses"
  20,20,"and he cast it down, and behold it was a serpent sliding"
  20,21,"Said He, 'Take it, and fear not; We will restore it to its first state"
  20,22,"Now clasp thy hand to thy arm-pit; it shall come forth white, without evil. That is a second sign"
  20,23,So We would show thee some of Our greatest signs
  20,24,Go to Pharaoh; he has waxed insolent